"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 288 3 "kp " }{TEXT -1 96 "  I am willing to
 buy this.  But wasn't it a lot of work?  Is there another way?  An ea
sier way?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
3 "6. " }{TEXT 267 33 "Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic" }{TEXT -1 
148 ".  The Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic states that every intege
r can be factored in a unique way into a product of powers of primes. \+
 For example:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 5 "84 = " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^2*``(3)*``(7);" "6#*(-%!G6#\"
\"#F'-F%6#\"\"$\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"(F+" }{TEXT -1 4 " ;  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 9 "28490 =  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)*``(5)*``(7)*``(11)*``(3
7);" "6#*,-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"&F(-F%6#\"\"(F(-F%6#\"#6F(-F%6#\"#
PF(" }{TEXT -1 4 " ;  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 21 "581325814248300
0  =  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^3*``(3)^4*``(5)^3*``(11)^2*``(23)^3*``(2
9)*``(41)^2;" "6#*0-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"$-F%6#F(\"\"%-F%6#\"\"&F(-F%6#\"#6F'
-F%6#\"#BF(-F%6#\"#H\"\"\"-F%6#\"#TF'" }{TEXT -1 4 " .  " }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 17 "It is called the \+
" }{TEXT 270 11 "Fundamental" }{TEXT -1 217 " Theorem of Arithmetic be
cause of the role it plays in both simple and deep results in algebra \+
and number theory.  There are numerous and important facts which follo
w because of  the Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 10 "          " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 111 "Use paper a
nd pencil to factor the following integers into their prime decomposit
ions:  340340, 38*865, 10!.   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 266 8 "Answers:" }{TEXT 285 66 "340340=2^2*5*7*1
1*13*17;   38*865=2*5*19*173;  10! = 2^8*3^4*5^2*7" }{TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The Maple
 command  " }{TEXT 268 7 "ifactor" }{TEXT -1 32 " does this automatica
lly.   Use " }{TEXT 269 7 "ifactor" }{TEXT -1 102 " to verify your res
ults from above.  Now factor the following numbers:  384*8650,  10!+1 \+
,  your ss#. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "ifactor(340340);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
